Re-payment schedule or rules, defining how the credit has to be paid back.
Examples:
Closed-end loan - the schedule says how many re-payments have to be done and when, what is the amount of each re-payment (e.g. re-paying 10% of the provided credit, in 10 payments of CZK 1.000, by the 15th day of each month starting 15.12.2015)
Credit card - the schedule tells how much and to which date has to be paid (e.g. pay at least 3% of the debt by the 15th day of each month)
